#!/bin/bash

#=============================================================================================================
#
#	rv_route_test.sh [int [route]]
#
#	tests every basic route the system, using the RouteValidation component of the CoreTCMS
#	system. When there are multiple basic routes between two signals, all tracks that are
#	use by other routes but not by the current route will be blocked, so that RouteValidation
#	will set the correct route.
#
#	The program get the status of tracks, points, and signals from RailwayStateManager,
#	and if it finds any thing not as expected, it will reports the error.
#
#	arguments:
#		int .............. the interlocking name
#		route ............ the route name
#
#	note:
#		1. 	if not argument is specified, then all routes for every interlocking
#			will be tested
#		2.	if only the interlocking name is given, then all routes in the 
#			interlocking will be tested
#		3. 	when specifying a route, the route name will always starts with an "R".
#			but you can specify only part of the route id. In this case, all routes
#			which share the same name would tested. For example, R775 will test all
#			routes from R775A, R775B, R775C, etc.
#
#	Good luck!
#
#	This program is generated by "bridge.jar" by Hlee
#	Date: Wed 8/Jun/2011
#
#=============================================================================================================

